@antibearthesis $725b in revenue but at what cost...?

They have 2.5% gross margins.

Anthropic has 40% gross margins and both their run rate and their margins are increasing substantially month over month.

@edwardlando The issue isn’t whether OpenAI or Anthropic survive.

It’s whether they can return venture-scale money after burning huge sums in a market where models commoditise, switching costs are low, and powerful competitors have other ways to monetise.

Great product ≠ great investment.
